The current owner on record with the City of Boston for 3 Chamblet St is April Washington. The petition that the BPRD received has April Washington name  address and signature requesting trees to be planted in front of this location. As a result of this petition the street was inspected for new trees to be planted. It was then found that two trees could be planted at this location. At the time of the inspection a green door hanger was left behind stating the site was inspected for a new tree to be planted. This Spring a letter was also sent by the BPRD to the owner of 3 Chamblet St  April Washington that stated a tree would be planted at this location. April Washing also called the BPRD this morning and spoke with one of the Arborists who explained to her why the trees were being planted and how she had requested and signed a petition requesting the trees. At this time the trees on Chamblet St will be planted.
